1. Sol Strategies, the "Solana version of MicroStrategy", increased its holdings by 12,456 SOLs;
2. The CEO of the Hong Kong Securities Regulatory Commission: A crypto regulatory roadmap will be released today, focusing on protecting investors and covering different participants;
3. A whale withdrew 1,444 cbBTC from Coinbase in the past two weeks, deposited it into Aave, borrowed 29,025 ETH, and then deposited it into Binance;
4. Abraxas Capital Mgmt's associated address deposited a total of 24,810 ETH into the exchange in the past 24 hours;
5. CZ: All funds received in the donation wallet will be donated, possibly to those who lost money on TST or Broccolis;
6. Coinbase and its executives were sued by shareholders, claiming that they misled investors about bankruptcy risks and violated securities laws;
7. Court documents disclosed the breakdown of SBF's confiscated assets, including approximately $1 billion in financial assets and two private jets;
8. Wintermute Plans to expand in the United States and open an office in New York;
9. UniSat will launch Hexa, a hybrid trading engine dedicated to Bitcoin assets;
10. Chain week trading volume has continued to shrink since mid-January, and is still dominated by Solana;
11. Semler Scientific Q4 net income increased to nearly US$300 million due to the use of new accounting rules to calculate Bitcoin holdings;
12. Brevan Howard CEO: The crypto industry has turned a page after the FTX collapse, but risk management is still needed around the clock.
